tatami.core.agent.parametric

Class AgentParameters

  • java.lang.Object
    • tatami.core.agent.parametric.AgentParameters
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class AgentParameters
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    An instance of class stores the parameters of an agent (usually given at creation of the agent).

    The class is underpinned by a set of map entries, it is therefore possible to add multiple entries with the same key.

    The entries can have as name / key one of AgentParameterName or can be a String, for the so-called 'unregistered parameters'.

    The values of the entries are Object instances, but they are usually perceived as String or non-String. Specialized methods exist to retrieve String values.

    Author:
    Andrei Olaru

      • getUnregisteredParameters

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> getUnregisteredParameters()
        Method to retrieve a map of those parameters which are 'unregistered', i.e. their name is not the name of an AgentParameterName instance. Multiple entries for the same key will be ignored.
        Returns:
        a Map (ergo, no duplicate unregistered parameters allowed) with parameters whose names are not in AgentParameterName.
